location.fullValue: Horizon Plan, Red Rocks Ranch : The Skyline Collection

data.description: Remarkable cul-de-sac home in Friendly Hills on a rare 1/4 acre lot, all in the backyard! The home is bright, spacious, open and updated. The sunny top floor offers a spacious primary suite with a private southwest facing deck, a large second bedroom, a 3/4 second bathroom and a spacious loft area that can serve more than one purpose including living area, fitness, office and storage. The open main level includes two more rooms, garage access, laundry and a full bathroom, and flows nicely from the family room with a gas fireplace to the large and sunny formal dining room, to the extravagant, gourmet kitchen with lots of windows, counterspace, cabinet space and eating spaces at both the island and very sunny breakfast nook. The full basement is unfinished, but clean, stubbed for plumbing and plenty of ceiling height including a dropped area big enough for a golf simulator as previously used. The backyard is like a park offering several features including one patio with a hot tub, raised garden beds and lawn, both with subsurface drip irrigation, a tree-covered patio, and a zip-line! It begins with traditional grass behind the house and climbs up the hill where the trees and a more natural landscape take over. Plenty of space, privacy and shade. You can't beat the quiet and serene Morrison location, right next to the neighborhood path, walking distance to Lake Harriman, quick access to the mountains and foothills and still under 30 minutes to downtown Denver and the Denver Tech Center (DTC). Check out the Foothills Park and Rec district, and everything it has to offer! All information contained herein may be deemed reliable, but not guaranteed and is subject to change without notice. It is up to you to verify any and all information, in advertising or otherwise.
